{"TopicId":143708,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Make the Orbital Markers Automatically stick","CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T12:31:35Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T12:31:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis has been a long time requested feature, and that\u0027s for the orbital markers (such as apoapsis, periapsis, closest approach, etc) easier to keep the info up and right now I\u0027ve hit a situation where I want to go to Duna but I want to make a maneuver node so I know where and how long to burn but the thing won\u0027t stay put because either it clicks the orbital path and attempts to make a maneuver node or selects Duna, or worse, simply do nothing. This is really a problem for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone else feel the same?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould someone please make a quick \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patch fix or something as I need this functionality BAD right now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T12:55:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight click the markers to make them stay visible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-13T13:09:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222674153\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022143708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221468414523\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ips